Sam's Club Membership Offer

I meant to reply earlier, but the afternoon got away from me and I was trying to finish a few things before stepping outside for a break.

I did end up taking that longer walk, and it helped more than I expected. The weather was mild, the sidewalks were quiet, and I finally had space to think without jumping between tasks.

I also tried reorganizing the desk the way you suggested, and it actually made the room feel calmer. I moved the lamp to the corner, cleared the pile of papers, and put the notebook where I can reach it without leaning over everything else.

Now the whole space feels easier to use, which is probably why I stayed focused longer tonight. I still need to put away that stack by the chair, but at least the room no longer feels busy from every angle.

Anyway, thanks again for asking. I am doing alright, just trying to make the week feel a little less scattered and a little more manageable.

